lime juice
garlic powder
salt
dried apples
tyme
procutto
brown mustard
pork tenderloin
puff pastry

preheat oven at 400 degrees. bundle puff pastry in towel and let thaw.
process apples in mill until rough chopped.
marinate pork in lime juice, garlic powder, salt.

cut the loin length wise.

on parchment paper, roll the procutto out in a sheet with another sheet of parchment on top. 
Put the loin on the procutto, put the apple, tyme in the pork crack, and roll up.
Add mustard on the pastry and roll up the pork, adding egg wash to hold it.
brush roll with egg wash, and sprinkle with salt. Cook in oven until 140 degrees inside.
